==Korean==
===Etymology===
===Noun===
'''불''' (bul) cf. Old English ''[[bœl]]''
#[[fire]], [[flame]] (cf. Dutch [[vuur]], Greek ''pyr'')
#[[light]]
#[[furnace]], [[fireplace]]
#[[testicle]], [[testis]] 

====Derived terms====
*불[[길]] (-gil) [[flame]]
*불[[꽃]] (-kkoch) [[flame]], [[flare]]
*불[[똥]] (-ttong) [[spark]]
*불[[바다]] (-bada) [[widespread]] fire
*불[[붙]]다 (-butda) to [[catch on fire]]
*불[[빛]] (-bich) [[light]], color of fire 
*불[[사르]]다 (-sareuda) to [[burn]]
*불[[장난]] (-jangnan) [[playing]] with fire or love 
*불[[지르]]다 (-jireuda) to [[set on fire]]
*불[[쬐]]다 (-jjoeda) to [[warm]] (oneself at the fire)
*불[[켜]]다 (-kyeoda) to [[light]] (a candle or lamp)
*불[[타]]다 (-tada) to [[burn]], [[blaze]]
*불[[태우]]다 (-taeUda) to [[burn]]
*불[[피우]]다 (-piuda) to [[make a fire]]

====Related terms====
*불[[까]]다 (-kkada) to [[castrate]]
*불[[알]] (-al) [[testicle]], [[testis]]

===Verb===
'''불다''' (bulda)
# to [[blow]]
# to [[confess]]

====Derived terms====
*불어[[나]]다 (bulEo-nada) to [[increase]]
*불어[[넣]]다 (bulEo-neohda) to [[inspire]]

====Related terms====
*[[부르]]다 (bureuda) to be [[full]]; [[call]] 
*[[부풀]]다 (bupulda) to [[bulge]]
*[[부피]] (bupi) [[volume]]
*[[불룩]][[하]]다 (bullug-hada) to be [[bulging]], [[bulgy]], [[inflated]], [[swollen]]
*[[불리]]다 (bullida) to [[fill]]; [[harden]] (metal); [[soak]]; be called
*[[풀무]] (pulmu) [[bellows]], [[blower]] (cf. Latin [[pulmo]] "lung") 

